b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Krisp is best suited for remote workers on calls, noisy environment meetings, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Speechify, meanwhile, shines for reading text content aloud, accessibility, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Krisp describes itself as \"AI noise cancellation for calls and meetings.\" Speechify, established in 2017, positions itself as \"Listen to anything with natural-sounding AI voices.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Krisp** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Speechify is a poor choice — far from it. Speechify excels in its own right, particularly for reading text content aloud and accessibility.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class noise cancellation, go with Krisp. If great browser extension matters more to you, Speechify is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
